===Etymology===
From Neo-Latin [[glagoliticus]] < Serbo-Croatian [[glagoljica]]/[[глагољица]] < [[Old Church Slavonic|OCS]] [[глагол|глаголъ]] ("word" or "sound").

===Noun phrase===
#An [[alphabet]] designed in the ninth century [[CE]] by Saint Cyril in order to translate the [[Bible]] and other texts into [[Old Church Slavonic]].  It was later replaced by the [[Cyrillic alphabet]].  It is still in use in the Croatian Church along the [[Dalmatia]]n coast.

====Synonyms====
*[[Glagolitic]], [[Bukvitsa]] (''rare''), [[Glagolitsa]], [[Hieronymian]], [[Illyrian]] (''rare''), [[Slovenish]]

